# DevOps & CI/CD — Bunyan

## CI Pipeline (Required)

All changes must pass:

```bash
composer run lint && composer run test && npm run lint && npm run typecheck && npm run test
```

## GitHub Actions

- Pin all actions to SHA, not tags
- Use `permissions:` block (least-privilege)
- Never store secrets in code — use GitHub Secrets
- Separate workflows for: lint, test, deploy
- Matrix testing for PHP versions if applicable

## Docker

- Multi-stage builds for production images
- Non-root user in containers
- `.dockerignore` must exclude: `.git`, `node_modules`, `vendor`, `.env`
- Health checks on all services

## Deployment Strategy

- Zero-downtime deployments
- Run migrations before code switch
- Rollback plan for every deployment
- Environment parity: dev ≈ staging ≈ production

## Environment

- `.env` files never committed
- `.env.example` always up to date
- Secrets rotated regularly

## Pre-commit Hooks

- PHP CS Fixer (formatting)
- PHPStan (static analysis)
- ESLint + TypeScript check
- `--no-verify` is FORBIDDEN
